Description: Unit tonne divided by the unit year with 365 days.

Name: torr per metre
Description: CGS (Centimetre_Gram_Second system) unit of the pressure divided by the SI base unit metre.

Name: total acid number
Description: A unit of chemistry defining the amount of potassium hydroxide (KOH) in milligrams that is needed to neutralize the acids in one gram of oil. It is an important quality measurement of crude oil.

Name: tray or tray pack
Description: Use UN/ECE Recommendation 21 (refer to Note 2 in the spreadsheet introduction 1st sheet).

Name: treatment
Description: A unit of count defining the number of treatments (treatment: subjection to the action of a chemical physical or biological agent).

Name: trip
Description: A unit of count defining the number of trips.

Name: tropical year
Description: Unit of time equal to about 365.242 19 days. Synonym: solar year

Name: tube
Description: Use UN/ECE Recommendation 21 (refer to Note 2 in the spreadsheet introduction 1st sheet).

Name: twenty foot container
Description: A unit of count defining the number of shipping containers that measure 20 foot in length.

Name: tyre
Description: A unit of count defining the number of tyres (a solid or air_filled covering placed around a wheel rim to form a soft contact with the road absorb shock and provide traction).

Name: unit pole
Description: CGS (Centimetre_Gram_Second system) unit for magnetic flux of a magnetic pole (according to the interaction of identical poles of 1 dyn at a distance of a cm).

Name: use
Description: A unit of count defining the number of times an object is used.

Name: var
Description: The name of the unit is an acronym for volt_ampere_reactive.

Name: vial
Description: Use UN/ECE Recommendation 21 (refer to Note 2 in the spreadsheet introduction 1st sheet).

Name: volt AC
Description: A unit of electric potential in relation to alternating current (AC).

Name: volt DC
Description: A unit of electric potential in relation to direct current (DC).

Name: volt per pascal
Description: Derived SI unit volt divided by the derived SI unit pascal.

Name: water horse power
Description: A unit of power defining the amount of power required to move a given volume of water against acceleration of gravity to a specified elevation (pressure head).

Name: watt per metre degree Celsius
Description: Derived SI unit watt divided by the product of the SI base unit metre and the unit for temperature degree Celsius.

Name: watt per square centimetre
Description: Derived SI unit watt divided by the power of the 001_fold the SI base unit metre by exponent 2.

Name: watt per square inch
Description: Derived SI unit watt divided by the power of the unit inch according to the Anglo_American and Imperial system of units by exponent 2.

Name: watt per square metre kelvin to the fourth power
weber metre
Description: Product of the derived SI unit weber and SI base unit metre.

Name: weber to the power minus one
Description: Complement of the derived SI unit weber as unit of the Josephson constant which value is equal to the 384 597891_fold of the reference value gigahertz divided by volt.

Name: well
Description: A unit of count defining the number of wells.

Name: wet kilo
Description: A unit of mass defining the number of kilograms of a product including the water content of the product.

Name: wet pound
Description: A unit of mass defining the number of pounds of a material including the water content of the material.

Name: wet ton
Description: A unit of mass defining the number of tons of a material including the water content of the material.

Name: wine gallon
Description: A unit of volume equal to 231 cubic inches.

Name: working day
Description: A unit of count defining the number of working days (working day: a day on which work is ordinarily performed).

Name: working month
Description: A unit of time defining the number of working months.

Name: yard per hour
Description: Unit yard according to the Anglo_American and Imperial system of units divided by the unit hour.

Name: yard per minute
Description: Unit yard according to the Anglo_American and Imperial system of units divided by the unit minute.

Name: yard per second
Description: Unit yard according to the Anglo_American and Imperial system of units divided by the SI base unit second.

Name: yard per second squared
Description: Unit of the length according to the Anglo_American and Imperial system of units divided by the power of the SI base unit second by exponent 2.

Name: year
Description: Unit of time equal to 36525 days. Synonym: Julian year

Name: zone
Description: A unit of count defining the number of zones.
